In article <Bz0E9M.DMn@lila.com> dorsey@lila.com (Bill Dorsey) writes:
>[...] encrypted radios [using] DES encryption (presumably in ECB mode to
>allow recovery from the occasional corrupt data).


All DES modes allow recovery from corrupt data.  CBC is very good at it.
CFB might have a problem if you lost count of the number of bytes, but
there's no reason to use ECB.

